it is very likely that Michael-David Sasson is the right person to contact (but someone else should confirm). His email is msasson@eecs.berkeley.edu

 It is typically helpful if you cc your URAP advisor  on the email so that they can confirm that you are their student.

history.content:
You definitely need to contact the department if you want EE or CS 199 units, but I'm not aware what needs to be done for UGIS. If you are a CS major, perhaps it would be helpful to show the language you saw to your CS adviser (either Charlene, Lily or Christopher). 

Thanks!

I got selected for a URAP position this semester, and I have decided to enroll in UGIS 192 for units. When I was reading the learning contract, it said that I needed to contact the department to arrange for those units. Since I am working for an EECS professor, I was wondering who exactly should I contact.

Also, I was wondering if the URAP satisfies any upper division requirements for the CS Major (College of L&S).
